# Resume Hacker – Environment Variables
#
# ── Local development ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the keys for the providers you want
# to use. Ollama (local) does not require an API key.
#
# ── Vercel deployment ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Do NOT commit `.env.local`. Instead, add keys via the Vercel Dashboard:
#   Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# Ollama is not available on Vercel — use a cloud provider below.

# OpenAI (gpt-4o, gpt-4-turbo, gpt-3.5-turbo …)
OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-your-openai-api-key"

# Anthropic (claude-3-5-sonnet, claude-3-opus …)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-your-anthropic-api-key"

# Google Gemini (gemini-1.5-pro, gemini-flash …)
GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY="your-google-api-key"

# DeepSeek (deepseek-chat, deepseek-reasoner …)
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY="your-deepseek-api-key"
